# Cron configuration for daily stock update
# 
# To install this cron job:
# 1. Copy this file to your EC2 instance
# 2. Run: crontab -e
# 3. Add the line below (adjust path and time as needed)
#
# Schedule: Daily at 2:00 AM UTC (adjust timezone as needed)
# 
# 0 2 * * * cd ~/tradingAssistant && /usr/bin/python3 run_daily_update_ec2.py >> logs/cron.log 2>&1
#
# Alternative schedules:
# - Daily at 2 AM UTC: 0 2 * * *
# - Daily at 6 AM UTC: 0 6 * * *
# - Every 12 hours: 0 */12 * * *
# - Weekdays only at 2 AM: 0 2 * * 1-5
#
# To view cron logs:
# tail -f ~/tradingAssistant/logs/cron.log

# Recommended cron entry (uncomment and adjust):
# 0 2 * * * cd ~/tradingAssistant && /usr/bin/python3 run_daily_update_ec2.py >> logs/cron.log 2>&1

